#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn22.7"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn22.7:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 22 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 22 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.7:0.2"
msgid "1. Nakulapituvagga "
msgstr "1. Nakula’s Father "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn22.7:0.3"
msgid "7. Upādāparitassanāsutta "
msgstr "7. Anxiety Because of Grasping "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli3.16, sc1
msgctxt "sn22.7:1.1"
msgid "Sāvatthinidānaṃ. "
msgstr "At Sāvatthī. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.7:1.2"
msgid "“Upādāparitassanañca vo, bhikkhave, desessāmi anupādāaparitassanañca. "
msgstr "“Mendicants, I will teach you how grasping leads to anxiety, and how not grasping leads to freedom from anxiety. "

msgctxt "sn22.7:1.3"
msgid "Taṃ suṇātha, sādhukaṃ manasi karotha, bhāsissāmī”ti. "
msgstr "Listen and pay close attention, I will speak.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.7:1.4"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”ti, kho te bhikkhū bhagavato paccassosuṃ. "
msgstr "“Yes, sir,” they replied. "

msgctxt "sn22.7:1.5"
msgid "Bhagavā etadavoca: "
msgstr "The Buddha said this: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "sn22.7:2.1"
msgid "“Kathañca, bhikkhave, upādāparitassanā hoti? "
msgstr "“And how does grasping lead to anxiety? "

msgctxt "sn22.7:2.2"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, assutavā puthujjano ariyānaṃ adassāvī ariyadhammassa akovido ariyadhamme avinīto, sappurisānaṃ adassāvī sappurisadhammassa akovido sappurisadhamme avinīto "
msgstr "It’s when an uneducated ordinary person has not seen the noble ones, and is neither skilled nor trained in the teaching of the noble ones. They’ve not seen good persons, and are neither skilled nor trained in the teaching of the good persons. "

msgctxt "sn22.7:2.3"
msgid "rūpaṃ attato samanupassati, rūpavantaṃ vā attānaṃ; attani vā rūpaṃ, rūpasmiṃ vā attānaṃ. "
msgstr "They regard form as self, self as having form, form in self, or self in form. "

msgctxt "sn22.7:2.4"
msgid "Tassa taṃ rūpaṃ vipariṇamati aññathā hoti. "
msgstr "But that form of theirs decays and perishes, "

msgctxt "sn22.7:2.5"
msgid "Tassa rūpavipariṇāmaññathābhāvā rūpavipariṇāmānuparivatti viññāṇaṃ hoti. "
msgstr "and consciousness latches on to the perishing of form. "

# NOTE: See https://discourse.suttacentral.net/t/parallels-and-translation-of-sn-22-7-help/2926
msgctxt "sn22.7:2.6"
msgid "Tassa rūpavipariṇāmānuparivattijā paritassanā dhammasamuppādā cittaṃ pariyādāya tiṭṭhanti. "
msgstr "Anxieties occupy their mind, born of latching on to the perishing of form, and originating in accordance with natural principles. "

msgctxt "sn22.7:2.7"
msgid "Cetaso pariyādānā uttāsavā ca hoti vighātavā ca apekkhavā ca upādāya ca paritassati. "
msgstr "So they become frightened, worried, concerned, and anxious because of grasping. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "sn22.7:3.1"
msgid "Vedanaṃ attato samanupassati, vedanāvantaṃ vā attānaṃ; attani vā vedanaṃ, vedanāya vā attānaṃ. "
msgstr "They regard feeling as self … "

msgctxt "sn22.7:3.2"
msgid "Tassa sā vedanā vipariṇamati aññathā hoti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn22.7:3.3"
msgid "Tassa vedanāvipariṇāmaññathābhāvā vedanāvipariṇāmānuparivatti viññāṇaṃ hoti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn22.7:3.4"
msgid "Tassa vedanāvipariṇāmānuparivattijā paritassanā dhammasamuppādā cittaṃ pariyādāya tiṭṭhanti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn22.7:3.5"
msgid "Cetaso pariyādānā uttāsavā ca hoti vighātavā ca apekkhavā ca upādāya ca paritassati. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "sn22.7:4.1"
msgid "Saññaṃ attato samanupassati … pe … "
msgstr "They regard perception as self … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.7:4.2"
msgid "saṅkhāre attato samanupassati, saṅkhāravantaṃ vā attānaṃ; attani vā saṅkhāre, saṅkhāresu vā attānaṃ. "
msgstr "They regard choices as self … "

msgctxt "sn22.7:4.3"
msgid "Tassa te saṅkhārā vipariṇamanti aññathā honti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn22.7:4.4"
msgid "Tassa saṅkhāravipariṇāmaññathābhāvā saṅkhāravipariṇāmānuparivatti viññāṇaṃ hoti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn22.7:4.5"
msgid "Tassa saṅkhāravipariṇāmānuparivattijā paritassanā dhammasamuppādā cittaṃ pariyādāya tiṭṭhanti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn22.7:4.6"
msgid "Cetaso pariyādānā uttāsavā ca hoti vighātavā ca apekkhavā ca upādāya ca paritassati. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli3.17, sc5
msgctxt "sn22.7:5.1"
msgid "Viññāṇaṃ attato samanupassati, viññāṇavantaṃ vā attānaṃ; attani vā viññāṇaṃ, viññāṇasmiṃ vā attānaṃ. "
msgstr "They regard consciousness as self, self as having consciousness, consciousness in self, or self in consciousness. "

msgctxt "sn22.7:5.2"
msgid "Tassa taṃ viññāṇaṃ vipariṇamati aññathā hoti. "
msgstr "But that consciousness of theirs decays and perishes, "

msgctxt "sn22.7:5.3"
msgid "Tassa viññāṇavipariṇāmaññathābhāvā viññāṇavipariṇāmānuparivatti viññāṇaṃ hoti. "
msgstr "and consciousness latches on to the perishing of consciousness. "

msgctxt "sn22.7:5.4"
msgid "Tassa viññāṇavipariṇāmānuparivattijā paritassanā dhammasamuppādā cittaṃ pariyādāya tiṭṭhanti. "
msgstr "Anxieties occupy their mind, born of latching on to the perishing of consciousness, and originating in accordance with natural principles. "

msgctxt "sn22.7:5.5"
msgid "Cetaso pariyādānā uttāsavā ca hoti vighātavā ca apekkhavā ca upādāya ca paritassati. "
msgstr "So they become frightened, worried, concerned, and anxious because of grasping. "

msgctxt "sn22.7:5.6"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, upādāparitassanā hoti. "
msgstr "That’s how grasping leads to anxiety. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc6
msgctxt "sn22.7:6.1"
msgid "Kathañca, bhikkhave, anupādāaparitassanā hoti? "
msgstr "And how does not grasping lead to freedom from anxiety? "

msgctxt "sn22.7:6.2"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, sutavā ariyasāvako ariyānaṃ dassāvī ariyadhammassa kovido ariyadhamme suvinīto, sappurisānaṃ dassāvī sappurisadhammassa kovido sappurisadhamme suvinīto "
msgstr "It’s when an educated noble disciple has seen the noble ones, and is skilled and trained in the teaching of the noble ones. They’ve seen good persons, and are skilled and trained in the teaching of the good persons. "

msgctxt "sn22.7:6.3"
msgid "na rūpaṃ attato samanupassati, na rūpavantaṃ vā attānaṃ; na attani vā rūpaṃ, na rūpasmiṃ vā attānaṃ. "
msgstr "They don’t regard form as self, self as having form, form in self, or self in form. "

msgctxt "sn22.7:6.4"
msgid "Tassa taṃ rūpaṃ vipariṇamati aññathā hoti. "
msgstr "When that form of theirs decays and perishes, "

msgctxt "sn22.7:6.5"
msgid "Tassa rūpavipariṇāmaññathābhāvā na rūpavipariṇāmānuparivatti viññāṇaṃ hoti. "
msgstr "consciousness doesn’t latch on to the perishing of form. "

msgctxt "sn22.7:6.6"
msgid "Tassa na rūpavipariṇāmānuparivattijā paritassanā dhammasamuppādā cittaṃ pariyādāya tiṭṭhanti. "
msgstr "Anxieties—born of latching on to the perishing of form and originating in accordance with natural principles—don’t occupy their mind. "

#. VAR: na cevuttāsavā → na ceva uttāsavā (bj, s1-3, pts1, mr) | na ca uttāsavā (si)
msgctxt "sn22.7:6.7"
msgid "Cetaso apariyādānā na cevuttāsavā hoti na ca vighātavā na ca apekkhavā, anupādāya ca na paritassati. "
msgstr "So they don’t become frightened, worried, concerned, or anxious because of grasping. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc7
msgctxt "sn22.7:7.1"
msgid "Na vedanaṃ attato samanupassati, na vedanāvantaṃ vā attānaṃ; na attani vā vedanaṃ, na vedanāya vā attānaṃ. "
msgstr "They don’t regard feeling as self … "

msgctxt "sn22.7:7.2"
msgid "Tassa sā vedanā vipariṇamati aññathā hoti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn22.7:7.3"
msgid "Tassa vedanāvipariṇāmaññathābhāvā na vedanāvipariṇāmānuparivatti viññāṇaṃ hoti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn22.7:7.4"
msgid "Tassa na vedanāvipariṇāmānuparivattijā paritassanā dhammasamuppādā cittaṃ pariyādāya tiṭṭhanti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn22.7:7.5"
msgid "Cetaso apariyādānā na cevuttāsavā hoti na ca vighātavā na ca apekkhavā, anupādāya ca na paritassati. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli3.18, sc8
msgctxt "sn22.7:8.1"
msgid "Na saññaṃ … pe … na saṅkhāre attato samanupassati, "
msgstr "They don’t regard perception as self … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.7:8.2"
msgid "na attani vā saṅkhāre, na saṅkhāresu vā attānaṃ. "
msgstr "They don’t regard choices as self … "

msgctxt "sn22.7:8.3"
msgid "na saṅkhāravantaṃ vā attānaṃ; "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn22.7:8.4"
msgid "Tassa te saṅkhārā vipariṇamanti aññathā honti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn22.7:8.5"
msgid "Tassa saṅkhāravipariṇāmaññathābhāvā na saṅkhāravipariṇāmānuparivatti viññāṇaṃ hoti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn22.7:8.6"
msgid "Tassa na saṅkhāravipariṇāmānuparivattijā paritassanā dhammasamuppādā cittaṃ pariyādāya tiṭṭhanti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn22.7:8.7"
msgid "Cetaso apariyādānā na cevuttāsavā hoti na ca vighātavā na ca apekkhavā, anupādāya ca na paritassati. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc9
msgctxt "sn22.7:9.1"
msgid "Na viññāṇaṃ attato samanupassati, na viññāṇavantaṃ vā attānaṃ … pe … "
msgstr "They don’t regard consciousness as self … "

msgctxt "sn22.7:9.2"
msgid "tassa taṃ viññāṇaṃ vipariṇamati aññathā hoti. "
msgstr "When that consciousness of theirs decays and perishes, "

msgctxt "sn22.7:9.3"
msgid "Tassa viññāṇavipariṇāmaññathābhāvā na viññāṇavipariṇāmānuparivatti viññāṇaṃ hoti. "
msgstr "consciousness doesn’t latch on to the perishing of consciousness. "

msgctxt "sn22.7:9.4"
msgid "Tassa na viññāṇavipariṇāmānuparivattijā paritassanā dhammasamuppādā cittaṃ pariyādāya tiṭṭhanti. "
msgstr "Anxieties—born of latching on to the perishing of consciousness and originating in accordance with natural principles—don’t occupy their mind. "

msgctxt "sn22.7:9.5"
msgid "Cetaso apariyādānā na cevuttāsavā hoti na ca vighātavā na ca apekkhavā, anupādāya ca na paritassati. "
msgstr "So they don’t become frightened, worried, concerned, or anxious because of grasping. "

msgctxt "sn22.7:9.6"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, anupādā aparitassanaṃ hotī”ti. "
msgstr "That’s how not grasping leads to freedom from anxiety.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn22.7:9.7"
msgid "Sattamaṃ. "
msgstr ""

